NOT my STORY

By Ennek
Summer of the Wolf
>3 short stories about young love and coming of Age b/w wolfess and human (contains smut)

https://www.sofurry.com/view/997398 (part 1)
https://www.sofurry.com/view/1022460 (part 2)
https://www.sofurry.com/view/1551023 (part 3)

I wrote a review thing on it and I want to know what yall think. As in if it is reasonable. For this is very well written, but I have just one inquiry and I think this piece will be kino. Review coming up (be sure to read it, it is rather short:

=========================================== Discussion ========================================

This is such a wonderful story! I look forward to more, if you decide to continue it. I have one question that is followed by a discussion.

Is it safe to assume that neither Anise nor Tim dated or had sexual encounters with other people in their 4 years apart?

I felt like that was the case because of how intimate and meaningful sex is to them and how the intensity of their copulation in her apartment was akin to the catharsis of two lonely souls finally able to connect to someone in flesh and spirit again after so many years. Furthermore, I think Anise emphasizing on how she never purposely meant to forget about him and being VERY apologetic, stating with 100% honesty and certainty that she never even thought about seeking out sexual/emotional partners besides him, would lead to a more smooth reunion. This makes if feel more like they were suffering together or to the same degree, rather than Tim’s misery being the result of her devaluing their relationship to the point where she is willing to replace him as a emotional/sexual partner with someone else, either through casual or committed hook-ups, in order to sustain her growing cynical view of humans. If we chose the latter, then we have to confront the fact that she is only coming back to him because nothing came out of those relationships.

Anonymous Sat 29 Feb 2020 17:56:08 No.28668199 Report

>>28666855
Kind of.
If you wanted to apply a hard scifi ethic to the situation, some digitrade animals have a longer foot (measured from ankle to toe) than we do as a percentage of leg length.
How you alter that to a foot with a less square aspect is up to you.
Evolution has taken multiple routes. The wrist/ankle joint can become more complex with an increased bone count. The previous ankle could fuse, and a new one could form from the existing tarsals.

A few nights reading and comparing human bone structure vs other primates, plus a working knowledge of mechanics should tell you there isn't a single right answer to bipedal leg structure.
We have the wrong musculature to lift ourselves from a squat at maximal force while in a digitrade stance.
I think it could be done, but the tendon insertions would be different than ours, with less fine control
